Catherine Boitard

The rocket strike against the US embassy in Athens has revived fears of extreme- left violence , never completely eradicated despite the break-up of Greece 's main radical groups earlier this decade .

In the run-up to the Athens 2004 Olympics , the Greek police succeeded in dismantling the country 's two deadliest groups -- November 17 and the People 's Revolutionary Struggle ( ELA ) -- which had combined for a quarter-century of assassinations and attacks on police , banks and foreign interest targets .

Arson attacks against `` imperialist '' and `` capitalist '' targets continued from a variety of small groups , but in 2003 a new outfit emerged with the know-how to carry out more destructive strikes : Revolutionary Struggle ( EA ) .

